<paragraph id="6C441A7DFFDCFC7B0DBA4B442E42FD1F" blockId="13.[189,1399,608,705]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDCFC7B0DBA4B442AA3FDA5" author="Lacordaire" box="[189,407,608,634]" firstAuthor="Lacordaire" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref14156" refString="Lacordaire J. T. 1848. Monographie des coleopteres subpentameres de la famille des phytophages. Tome second. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege 5: i-vi + 1 - 890." type="book" year="1848">Lacordaire (1848)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDCFC7B0CE84B4429A2FDA5" box="[495,662,608,634]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Clythra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0CE84B4429A2FDA5" box="[495,662,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Clythra colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the species not known to him and reported it from “Promont. Bonae Spei” [= 
<collectingRegion id="AE3FD49FFFDCFC7B0CFD4BA72902FD42" box="[506,566,643,669]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cape</collectingRegion>
of Good Hope] although neither 
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDCFC7B0EBB4BA72FB0FD42" author="Thunberg" box="[956,1156,643,669]" firstAuthor="Thunberg" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref15904" refString="Thunberg C. P. 1787. D. D. Museum Naturalium Academiae Upsaliensis. Partem quartam. Joh. Edman, Uppsala." type="book" year="1787">Thunberg (1787)</bibRefCitation>
nor Forsberg (1821) provided any 
<typeStatus id="B340A4DFFFDCFC7B0C674B832AA7FD1E" box="[352,403,679,705]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality. Habitually, 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDCFC7B0F8D4B832878FD1F" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[650,844,678,704]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miopristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0F8D4B832878FD1F" box="[650,844,678,704]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Miopristis colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to many South African 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDCFC7B081C4B822E42FD1F" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[1307,1398,678,704]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Clytrini">Clytrini</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<caption id="38844AF5FFDCFC7B0DBA4E812812F83D" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651416/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" startId="13.[189,232,1957,1983]" targetBox="[189,1398,775,1911]" targetPageId="13">
