<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0C114E822AEEF860" box="[278,474,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Miopristis colon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDCFC7B0CEB4E81299AF860" author="Thunberg" box="[492,686,1957,1983]" firstAuthor="Thunberg" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="157 - 193" refId="ref15964" refString="Thunberg C. P. 1821. Coleoptera Capensia, antennis fusiformibus. Nova Acta Regiae Societatis Scientiarum Upsaliensis 8: 157 - 193." type="journal article" year="1821">Thunberg, 1821</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, ♀, 5.5 mm, UUZM. 
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B093E4E812F7AF860" bold="true" box="[1081,1102,1957,1983]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B09F84E812E27F860" bold="true" box="[1279,1299,1957,1983]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0C044EEC2A2CF83D" bold="true" box="[259,280,1992,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C</emphasis>
. ventral view. 
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0CC24EEC2AEEF83D" bold="true" box="[453,474,1992,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D</emphasis>
. Frontal view. 
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDCFC7B0F8C4EEC29ABF83D" bold="true" box="[651,671,1992,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E</emphasis>
. Box label.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6C441A7DFFDFFC780DBA482F2F14FE97" blockId="14.[189,1399,267,329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
which, in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDFFC780CF4482F29FEFEFA" author="Lacordaire" box="[499,714,267,293]" firstAuthor="Lacordaire" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref14156" refString="Lacordaire J. T. 1848. Monographie des coleopteres subpentameres de la famille des phytophages. Tome second. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege 5: i-vi + 1 - 890." type="book" year="1848">Lacordaire (1848)</bibRefCitation>
, allows me to believe that the 
<typeStatus id="B340A4DFFFDFFC780922482F2FB8FEFA" box="[1061,1164,267,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in the 
<collectingRegion id="AE3FD49FFFDFFC780DBA480B2BCDFE96" box="[189,249,303,329]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Cape</collectingRegion>
together with many other specimens during Thunberg’s expeditions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C441A7DFFDFFC780DBA48542F14FE72" blockId="14.[189,1398,368,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The 
<typeStatus id="B340A4DFFFDFFC780DF448542A6EFE55" box="[243,346,368,394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780C854854296DFE55" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" box="[386,601,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780C854854296DFE55" box="[386,601,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysomela colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not traced, or was overlooked, by 
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDFFC78092B48542E77FE55" author="Wallin &amp; Wallin" box="[1068,1347,368,394]" firstAuthor="Wallin" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref16123" refString="Wallin L. &amp; Wallin H. 2001. Catalogue of Type Specimens. 1. C. P. Thunberg (1743 - 1828), Insecta. Revised version 6. Uppsala University, Museum of Evolution, Zoology section (UUMZ). Available from: http: // www. evolutionsmuseet. uu. se / samling / UUZM 01 _ Thunberg. pdf [accessed 30 May 2018]." type="book" year="2001">Wallin &amp; Wallin (2001)</bibRefCitation>
and thus it lacks the typical printed red label they added to all type specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C441A7DFFDFFC780DBA48F129F5FCD7" blockId="14.[189,1399,468,777]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The species identity of 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780CCA48F12997FE30" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" box="[461,675,469,495]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780CCA48F12997FE30" box="[461,675,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysomela colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unclear. The 
<typeStatus id="B340A4DFFFDFFC780E5C48F128F6FE30" box="[859,962,469,495]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
is a relatively small female (
<quantity id="AB03B798FFDFFC78081548F02E5BFE30" box="[1298,1391,468,495]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
) with a reduced black elytral pattern. 
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDFFC780F8548DC28E5FDCC" author="Jacoby &amp; Clavareau" box="[642,977,504,531]" firstAuthor="Jacoby" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="49" refId="ref13987" refString="Jacoby M. &amp; Clavareau H. 1906. Coleoptera Phytophaga, Fam. Chrysomelidae, Subfam. Clytrinae. In: Wytsman P. (ed) Genera Insectorum. Fasc. 49. V. Verteneuil &amp; L. Desmet, Brussels." type="book chapter" year="1906">Jacoby &amp; Clavareau (1906)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="086A678CFFDFFC78091548DC2FD7FDCD" author="Clavareau" box="[1042,1251,504,530]" firstAuthor="Clavareau" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="6" refId="ref13190" refString="Clavareau H. 1913. Chrysomelidae: 5. Megascelinae, 6. Megalopodinae, 7. Clytrinae, 8. Cryptocephalinae, 9. Chlamydinae, 10. Lamprosominae. In: Schenkling S. (ed.) Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 53. W. Junk, Berlin." type="journal article" year="1913">Clavareau (1913)</bibRefCitation>
classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780DDA4B382A62FDEA" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1848" box="[221,342,540,565]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miopristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780DDA4B382A62FDEA" box="[221,342,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Miopristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with some doubt. Currently, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780E364B38289EFDEA" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1848" box="[817,938,540,565]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miopristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780E364B38289EFDEA" box="[817,938,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Miopristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises more than 20 species and I examined the primary type specimens of about 90% of the species. The colouration of 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC7809A54B1A2E42FD87" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" box="[1186,1398,574,600]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC7809A54B1A2E42FD87" box="[1186,1398,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysomela colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not exactly fit with any of the described species. However, as in many 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC7809504B452F81FDA4" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[1111,1205,609,635]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Clytrini">Clytrini</taxonomicName>
, the colouration of species of 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780C5A4BA12AE2FD41" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1848" box="[349,470,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miopristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780C5A4BA12AE2FD41" box="[349,470,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Miopristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely variable and I cannot exclude that the 
<typeStatus id="B340A4DFFFDFFC7809464BA12F9CFD40" box="[1089,1192,645,671]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC7809D64BA12E70FD40" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" box="[1233,1348,645,671]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC7809D64BA12E70FD40" box="[1233,1348,645,671]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ch. colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a pale specimen with reduced black pattern of some other already described species. In summary, I leave 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780DBA4BEF2AA7FD3A" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" box="[189,403,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysomela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colon">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780DBA4BEF2AA7FD3A" box="[189,403,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Chrysomela colon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species in 
<taxonomicName id="ABFB61FEFFDFFC780F8A4BE82832FD3A" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1848" box="[653,774,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Miopristis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5E8FC66FFFDFFC780F8A4BE82832FD3A" box="[653,774,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Miopristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and its identity can be resolved in the future if more specimens, including males, are discovered.
</paragraph>
